==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nemesis
<hw>Nem"e*sis</hw> <pr>(n⟦ecr⟧m"⟦esl⟧*s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos>
<ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>Ne`mesis</grk>, orig., distribution, fr.
<grk>ne`mein</grk> to distribute. See <er>Nomad</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>The goddess of retribution or vengeance;
hence, retributive justice personified; divine vengeance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This is that ancient doctrine of <qex>nemesis</qex> who keeps
watch in the universe, and lets no offense go unchastised.</q>
<rj><qau>Emerson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nemophilist</ent>⟦br⟧
